<TITLE> BKMEA directors quit 'over poll delay' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 06 (bdnews24.com)  Six of 27 BKMEA directors have quit their posts in protest over a delay in annual elections to the knitwear industry association, one of the country's leading trade bodies. GM Faruk, Md Shah Newaz, Shafiquzzaman Prince, Hasan Mahmud, Md Anwar Hossain, Md Zakir Hossain resigned on Saturday, BKMEA president Fazlul Hoque told bdnews24.com. GM Faruk told bdnews24.com, "I along with five others quit as the association polls were not held in time." He said other directors were also going to resign. BKMEA secretary Sulav Chowdhury told bdnews24.com, "Six directors have submitted resignation letters. They expressed their personal opinions in the letters on the BKMEA election." In line with the BKMEA constitution, the election schedule was due to be declared in the first week of January. Over 200 members of the association submitted a memorandum to the association authorities on Jan 16 demanding immediate declaration of the schedule. On Jan 20, they submitted another memo to the commerce minister Faruk Khan bdn
